---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Applied Corporate Training | AI, Claude Code, Power BI, Excel | Lumina Consulting"
  description="Hands-on courses on generative AI (Claude, ChatGPT, Copilot), Claude Code, AI APIs (Anthropic, OpenAI), Power BI, and advanced Excel for your team. Practical, applied to your real business problems."
  lang="en"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "name": "Data Training",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Lumina Consulting",
      "url": "https://luminaconsulting.ai"
    },
    "description": "Corporate training in generative AI (Claude, ChatGPT, Copilot), Claude Code, AI APIs (Anthropic, OpenAI), Power BI, and advanced Excel. Practical courses with hands-on exercises using your real data.",
    "areaServed": ["CL", "LATAM"],
    "serviceType": "Corporate Training"
  })} />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative py-12 md:py-14 bg-lum-black overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-1/4 -right-32 w-96 h-96 bg-lum-coral/15 rounded-full blur-3xl" />
    </div>
    <div class="container-custom relative">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <a href="/en/services" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lum-slate-light hover:text-white mb-6 transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
          </svg>
          All services
        </a>
        <span class="badge bg-white/10 text-white border-white/20 mb-4">Training</span>
        <h1 class="text-white mb-6">Applied Corporate Training</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-lum-slate-light max-w-2xl">
          Hands-on courses on generative AI, Claude Code, AI APIs (Anthropic, OpenAI), Power BI, and advanced Excel. Not abstract theory: we work with your company's real data, processes, and problems. Taught by the same professor who teaches Advanced Data Analytics at Universidad de los Andes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why different -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="mb-8">Why this training is different</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-lum-slate mb-6">
          Most courses on tools like Power BI or Excel teach functions and buttons. The participant leaves knowing how to make a bar chart, but doesn't know how to apply it to their real work.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-lum-slate mb-6">
          I do things differently: before we start, I meet with you to understand what problems you have, what data you manage, and what decisions you need to make. Then I design the course using those real examples.
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-10">
          <div class="p-6 bg-lum-cream rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-600 mb-3">Traditional training</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-lum-slate">
              <li>• Generic textbook examples</li>
              <li>• Made-up data</li>
              <li>• Focused on functions and menus</li>
              <li>• Monday you're back at work and don't know where to start</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="p-6 bg-lum-cream rounded-xl">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lum-coral mb-3">My approach</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-lum-slate">
              <li>• Examples from your industry or company</li>
              <li>• Your real data (anonymized if needed)</li>
              <li>• Focused on solving business problems</li>
              <li>• Monday you already have something working</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Available courses -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-lum-cream">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="mb-10 text-center">Available courses</h2>

        <p class="text-mono-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-lum-coral mb-4">Generative AI</p>

        <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Generative AI for executives and boards</h3>
                <p class="text-lum-slate mb-4">
                  Strategic session aimed at CEOs, boards, and executive committees. What generative AI really is today, what changes in the business, what investment and risk decisions emerge, and how to talk to the technical team without jargon. Hands-off: the goal is for the top line to understand magnitude, not learn prompts.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Short session</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">In-person or online</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Board focus</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Generative AI applied by business area</h3>
                <p class="text-lum-slate mb-4">
                  Hands-on workshop for teams that already use, or want to start using, tools like Claude, ChatGPT, and Copilot in their day-to-day work. Cases contextualized by role: finance and management control, sales and marketing, operations, HR, legal. Prompt best practices, handling of sensitive data, integration with Office and Google Workspace, and building custom skills for repetitive tasks.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Hands-on workshop</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">In-person or online</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Adaptable by area</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Real data</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Claude Code and AI-assisted development for technical teams</h3>
                <p class="text-lum-slate mb-4">
                  Advanced course for analysts, engineers, and technical teams that want to accelerate their work with AI-assisted development. Intensive use of Claude Code to build scripts, automations, and analysis over local files; consuming Anthropic and OpenAI APIs to embed AI inside internal pipelines and tools; building agents with MCPs, skills, and subagents; working directly with Power BI files (.pbip) and notebooks to accelerate reporting. Focused on solid engineering habits, not demos.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Advanced</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Intensive hands-on</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">In-person or online</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Claude Code + APIs</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-mono-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-lum-coral mb-4">Data, BI, and analytics</p>

        <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Power BI for business users</h3>
                <p class="text-lum-slate mb-4">
                  From zero to creating useful dashboards. Data connection, basic modeling, visualizations, publishing, and automatic refresh. Designed for managers, analysts, and anyone who needs to make decisions with data. Adaptable to classic Power BI or .pbip files with AI-accelerated workflows.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">From zero</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">In-person or online</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">PL-300 ready</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Advanced Excel for data analysis</h3>
                <p class="text-lum-slate mb-4">
                  Pivot tables, lookup functions, array formulas, Power Query for automating data cleaning, integration with Power BI. For those who already use Excel but want to get much more out of it. Includes using Claude and Copilot inside Excel to accelerate analysis.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Intermediate to advanced</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">In-person or online</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Excel + AI</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Data analysis for decision making</h3>
                <p class="text-lum-slate mb-4">
                  Beyond the tools: how to frame business questions, choose what to measure, interpret data, and present conclusions effectively. Ideal for managers and team leaders who receive many reports and need to separate signal from noise.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">For leaders</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">In-person or online</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-mono-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-lum-coral mb-4">Custom design</p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6">
              <div class="flex-1">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Custom training</h3>
                <p class="text-lum-slate mb-4">
                  If no standard course fits what you need, we design one specifically for your team. Can combine topics, go deeper in specific areas, or focus on a concrete project. Structure, duration, format, and level are defined after a discovery call.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">Variable duration</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">In-person or online</span>
                  <span class="text-xs px-2 py-1 bg-lum-cream rounded">100% custom</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-sm text-lum-slate mt-10 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Duration, depth, and format are adjusted to the needs and level of the group. After a short conversation we propose a program and a budget.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What makes it effective -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="mb-8">What makes training effective</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-lum-slate mb-6">
          After years of corporate training, I've learned that what makes the difference isn't the amount of content covered, but how applicable it is to the participant's daily work.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-lum-cream rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-4">My training approach:</h3>
          <ol class="space-y-3 text-lum-slate">
            <li><strong>1.</strong> We define the course objectives and relevant real-world problems</li>
            <li><strong>2.</strong> I customize examples using your data (or industry-specific data)</li>
            <li><strong>3.</strong> Participants work on exercises they can reuse at work</li>
            <li><strong>4.</strong> We build something practical during the training</li>
            <li><strong>5.</strong> Post-training support to answer questions that come up later</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lum-slate">
          The result: participants leave with skills they can apply immediately, not just certificates to hang on the wall.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Formats -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-lum-cream">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="mb-10 text-center">Training formats</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">On-site at your company</h3>
            <p class="text-lum-slate text-sm mb-4">
              I come to your office with everything needed. Ideal for groups of 5-15 people. Allows working with your real data in the moment.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-lum-slate-light">
              <strong>Advantage:</strong> Maximum customization, fewer distractions for participants.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Live online</h3>
            <p class="text-lum-slate text-sm mb-4">
              Sessions via Zoom or Teams. Good for distributed teams or when in-person isn't possible. Just as interactive, with real-time exercises.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-lum-slate-light">
              <strong>Advantage:</strong> Flexibility, no travel costs, easy to record.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Intensive format</h3>
            <p class="text-lum-slate text-sm mb-4">
              2-3 consecutive days, full day. For when you need the team to learn quickly and apply immediately.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-lum-slate-light">
              <strong>Best for:</strong> Projects with deadlines, new teams, initiative kickoffs.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Extended format</h3>
            <p class="text-lum-slate text-sm mb-4">
              3-4 hour sessions, 1-2 times per week, over several weeks. Allows practicing between sessions and bringing real questions.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-lum-slate-light">
              <strong>Best for:</strong> Habit change, deep adoption, busy teams.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="mb-10">Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <details class="bg-lum-cream rounded-xl p-6 group">
            <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
              How many people can participate?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lum-slate">
              For it to be truly practical, I recommend groups of 5 to 12 people. More than 15 makes it difficult to give individual attention. If you have more people, we do parallel groups.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-lum-cream rounded-xl p-6 group">
            <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
              What do participants need to know beforehand?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lum-slate">
              For Power BI from scratch, they just need to know how to use a computer and basic Excel. For advanced Excel, they should know the basics (simple formulas, tables). I can do a preliminary assessment if there are doubts.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-lum-cream rounded-xl p-6 group">
            <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
              Do you provide support materials?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lum-slate">
              Yes. Each participant receives exercise files, a quick reference guide, and access to session recordings (for online format). I also include 30 days of email support for post-course questions.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-lum-cream rounded-xl p-6 group">
            <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
              How much does it cost?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lum-slate">
              It depends on the complexity. Always with a prior quote and clear scope before starting. Let's talk about your case.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-lum-cream rounded-xl p-6 group">
            <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
              Can training be done in English?
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lum-slate">
              Yes, all courses can be delivered in English or Spanish, depending on your team's needs. Materials and support are available in both languages.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-lum-black">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-white mb-6">Need to train your team?</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-lum-slate-light mb-8">
          Tell me what tools they use today, what they'd like to learn, and how many people there are. I'll propose a plan.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a
            href="https://wa.me/56991629095?text=Hello,%20I'm%20interested%20in%20learning%20more%20about%20Lumina%20Consulting%20services"
            target="_blank"
            class="btn-primary"
          >
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M17.472 14.382c-.297-.149-1.758-.867-2.03-.967-.273-.099-.471-.148-.67.15-.197.297-.767.966-.94 1.164-.173.199-.347.223-.644.075-.297-.15-1.255-.463-2.39-1.475-.883-.788-1.48-1.761-1.653-2.059-.173-.297-.018-.458.13-.606.134-.133.298-.347.446-.52.149-.174.198-.298.298-.497.099-.198.05-.371-.025-.52-.075-.149-.669-1.612-.916-2.207-.242-.579-.487-.5-.669-.51-.173-.008-.371-.01-.57-.01-.198 0-.52.074-.792.372-.272.297-1.04 1.016-1.04 2.479 0 1.462 1.065 2.875 1.213 3.074.149.198 2.096 3.2 5.077 4.487.709.306 1.262.489 1.694.625.712.227 1.36.195 1.871.118.571-.085 1.758-.719 2.006-1.413.248-.694.248-1.289.173-1.413-.074-.124-.272-.198-.57-.347m-5.421 7.403h-.004a9.87 9.87 0 01-5.031-1.378l-.361-.214-3.741.982.998-3.648-.235-.374a9.86 9.86 0 01-1.51-5.26c.001-5.45 4.436-9.884 9.888-9.884 2.64 0 5.122 1.03 6.988 2.898a9.825 9.825 0 012.893 6.994c-.003 5.45-4.437 9.884-9.885 9.884m8.413-18.297A11.815 11.815 0 0012.05 0C5.495 0 .16 5.335.157 11.892c0 2.096.547 4.142 1.588 5.945L.057 24l6.305-1.654a11.882 11.882 0 005.683 1.448h.005c6.554 0 11.89-5.335 11.893-11.893a11.821 11.821 0 00-3.48-8.413z"/>
            </svg>
            Contact via WhatsApp
          </a>
          <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-secondary bg-white/5 border-white/20 text-white hover:bg-white/10">
            Schedule a Call
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
